  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a tagine or heavy‑bottomed pot over medium heat.",
    "Add onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in garlic, cumin, coriander, and sumac, and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add butter beans, tamarind paste, lemon juice, and water, stirring to combine.",
    "Bring to a gentle simmer, cover, and cook for 35 minutes, checking for tenderness.",
    "Remove the lid, increase heat to high, and simmer for 5 minutes to thicken the sauce.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley and a drizzle of olive oil.",
    "Enjoy the fizzy, bouncy texture and bright flavors of this Middle Eastern tagine."
